Sentencas: GdBaFe2O5+delta doping with Ca to subsitute Ba in A site were prepared by the citric-nitrate process.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: The effects of different contents of Ca on the physical and chemical properties and electrochemical properties of GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+delta were investigated.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: It is shown that with the increasing of Ca content, GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+delta remains pure phase within the amount of doping is less than 20%, otherwise BaFe2O4 miscellaneous phase appears.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: The XPS result shows that the valence of Fe increases continuously, that is, Fe3+ continuously changes to Fe4+, as the content of Ca increases.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: According to the principle of conservation of charge, the oxygen content of the material increases continuously.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: However, with the further increase of Ca content, the high-speed oxygen conduction on the ab axis is affected when the Ba-O bond is destroyed to a certain degree, and the conduction velocity is significantly reduced (dominant factor), resulting the highest conductivity 9.57 S cm(-1) at Ca content of 10%.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application

Sentencas: With the increase of Ca content, electron hole and oxygen content in the material are increasing, also led to the continuous decrease of the polarization resistance of the material, when the Ca content ascended to 20%, the minimum polarization impedance will be to 0.0415 Omega cm(2), delta increases to 5.8199, and the polarization process increases.
Titulo: Performance of Ca-doped GdBa1-xCaxFe2O5+δ(x=0, 0.1) as cathode materials for IT-SOFC application
